Install and run Portainer, a web-based Docker container management UI, using Docker itself.

ðŸ§± Abstracted Docker Command:
docker run -d \
  -p 9000:9000 \
  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \
  portainer/portainer

âœ… Step-by-Step on Ubuntu:
Ensure Docker is running:
sudo systemctl start docker
Run Portainer:
docker run -d \
  -p 9000:9000 \
  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \
  portainer/portainer
-d: detached mode (runs in background)
-p 9000:9000: expose the UI on host port 9000
-v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock: give Portainer access to the Docker daemon

Access the Portainer Web UI:
Open this in your browser:

http://localhost:9000
Or use your host's IP address if you're connecting from another machine:

http://<your-host-ip>:9000
Set up an admin user and password on first access, then choose to manage the local Docker environment.
ðŸ§¼ Optional Cleanup Command
To stop and remove Portainer:

docker rm -f $(docker ps -q --filter ancestor=portainer/portainer)
